div.p:
Among NATO-related arrangements and
                            facilities, the study indicates that Greece places importance on the
                            following: 

—[1 line not declassified];

—participation in the NATO
                                    intelligence and communication system;

—continued participation in NATO’s infrastructure program;

—membership in the NATO
                                    Military Committee;

—participation in the full range of NATO planning; and



—retention of specific facilities such as airfields, naval
                                    bases, command and control facilities, and certain NATO training sites.
